-- Court Says Total Didn't Follow Procedure, Must Restart Flanders Refinery
-- David Whitehouse
-- 2010-06-30T12:03:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/court-says-total-didn-t-follow-procedure-must-restart-flanders-refinery.html

          
          
             Total SA must restart its Flanders
refinery within 15 days or face a fine of 100,000 euros a day, a
court in Douai, northern France said in a ruling.  
 The company failed to follow the correct consultation
procedure with unions, the court said.  
          
          


  


        